>> time required: 10 minutes
>> image: https://www.mybakingaddiction.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/spoon-in-hot-fudge-sauce-hero-720x720.jpg

In a #medium, heavy saucepan{} over medium heat, combine @heavy cream{2/3%cup}, @corn syrup{0.5%cup}, @dark brown sugar{0.33%cup}, @unsweetened cocoa powder{0.25%cup}, @salt{0.25%tsp}, and half of the @bittersweet chocolate{6%oz}. Bring the mixture to a boil, stirring until the chocolate pieces are completely melted.

Reduce heat and cook at a low boil, stirring occasionally, for about ~{5%minutes}. Remove the pan from the heat and add in @unsalted butter{2%Tbsp}, @vanilla{1%tsp}, and remaining chocolate, stirring until smooth.

Allow the sauce to cool down before serving.
